# Server on port 8051 — mandatory after changes

The user **always** wants the REMI Trip Planner server **rebuilt and restarted on `:8051`** after any agent-made changes that affect the app (Go under `cmd/` or `internal/`, `web/templates`, `web/static`, `migrations`, `go.mod`).

**Do this at the end of the task** unless the user explicitly says not to restart, or they are running **`air`** / `dev-watch` (hot reload) and you know it is already rebuilding for them.

## Windows (PowerShell)

From the **`REMI Trip Planner`** directory (module root with `go.mod`):

```powershell
$p = Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 8051 -State Listen -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object -First 1 -ExpandProperty OwningProcess
if ($p) { Stop-Process -Id $p -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue }
go build -o remi-server.exe ./cmd/server/
$env:APP_ADDR = ":8051"
Start-Process -FilePath ".\remi-server.exe" -WorkingDirectory (Get-Location) -WindowStyle Hidden
```

Confirm listen: `netstat -ano | findstr ":8051"` (or `Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 8051`).

## Do not

- End with “run it yourself” when you changed code — **run the restart** (unless `air` is handling it).
- Skip restart after template/CSS/JS-only edits — the running binary may not need rebuild, but **restarting** still picks up static files from disk; **rebuild** when Go changed.

Docker deploy (`docker compose`) is optional; the user’s standing preference for local dev is **native `go build` + `APP_ADDR=:8051`**.
